    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to souvenirs acquired at pilgrimage sites that served as tokens of accomplished pilgrimage. Such souvenirs include badges and ampullae sold at pilgrimage sites, and even more valuable objects taken or presented as gifts from the shrine.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046892/Grove Art Online (2003-2008)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar souvenirs die als bewijs van een afgelegde bedevaart dienden. Zo werden er insignes en ampullen als souvenir verkocht in het bedevaartsoord, maar ook kostbaardere voorwerpen werden meegenomen of als geschenk van de heilige plaats aangeboden.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指於朝聖地點購買的紀念品，作為完成朝聖的獎勵。有些紀念品包括徽章及兩耳細頸瓶，更甚者，從神殿裡取得更具價值的物品作為禮品。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
